cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of grounding natural language phrases in images, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an approach that extends Faster R-CNN, which is a popular object detection algorithm, indicating relevance to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) and hence cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves reasoning between similar phrases, which can be viewed as a form of information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
